thread.title: Powerful earthquake strikes Mindanao, Philippines

title: Powerful earthquake strikes Mindanao, Philippines

organizations.name: us national oceanic and atmospheric administration

text:
The quake hit at 1:03 in the morning on Saturday AEDT. Photo: USGS 
It caused widespread blackouts, several buildings to collapse and the closure of the airport in the capital, Surigao, due to cracks in the runway. 
"There is chaos. Many of those affected are in shock," Governor Sol Matugas said in an interview with a Manila radio station. 
"Many areas do not have electricity and the airport has been closed." 
The quake struck at a depth of 10km and its epicentre was about 13km east of Surigao, the US Geological Survey said. Advertisement 
The Pacific Tsunami Warning Centre of the US National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration said there was no tsunami threat. 
Renato Solidum, head of the Philippines' seismic agency, said 89 aftershocks had been recorded and more could be expected but they were unlikely to cause significant damage. 
Friday's quake was the strongest since the city was rocked by a 6.9 quake in 1879, Solidum said. 
People rushed to open spaces and spent the night in parks and shelter areas, according to radio reports. 
Power lines were down, water supply was interrupted, a bridge and a hotel collapsed and some homes were damaged, Surigao city councillor Rise Recabo told DZRH radio. 
The Philippines is on the geologically active Pacific Ring of Fire and experiences frequent earthquakes. 
Reuters
